import_workspace_from_tarball.description:
Takes a tarball in and import scripts, resources, and resource types from a tarball exported of a workspace.

Is used as webhook target for  the windmill-gh-action-deploy

message_slack.description: Send a message to a channel or person in the connected slack workspace

postgres_example.description: An example of how to use resources from scripts. In this example, we will query the demo database demodb that is set up by default on Windmill.

return_chart_as_image.description: This script showcase that image can be rendered from their base64 encoding when their dict key is "png"
return_chart_as_image.summary: Build seaborn charts and return a rendered image

return_table.description: An example of a script that return a table that can get rendered

triggered_from_slack_command.description: An example of a script that can be triggered from script and whom parameters fit exactly the one passed by the slack command trigger
